message.content:
1. The study is a follow-up to an initial trial conducted in 2010.
2. The initial trial was a randomized, double-blind controlled trial (RCT).
3. The initial trial involved 902 infants.
4. The infants in the initial trial were aged between 6–17 months.
5. The infants in the initial trial were from Lima, Peru.
6. The infants in the initial trial were given daily supplements.
7. Some infants were given iron (Fe) as a supplement.
8. Some infants were given multiple micronutrients (MMN) as a supplement.
9. The multiple micronutrients included zinc.
10. There were 451 infants in each supplement group in the initial trial.

messages.content:
Statement: This study was a follow-up to an initial randomized, double-blind controlled trial (RCT) in 2010 in which 902 infants, aged 6–17 months, from Lima, Peru, were given daily supplements of either iron (Fe) or multiple micronutrients (MMN) including zinc (451 in each group).
